I figured I would put it somewhere online, so if something bad happened I don't loose it...or if my music disappears (god forbid) getting it back wouldn't be so overwhelming...also, as a reference for trades etc etc...bear with me...ive never made a cut before

I haven't updated in a bit, but the last few days have been really fun, so I figured I would write them down.

I got back from wild fire last Monday, which was awesome. Everyone was super friendly and I learned a super lot of cool stuff. I spun fire poi and I liked it alot, so I started to buy hardware to make my own set. I won't be able to get Kevlar for a while, and I cant find the right kind of chain anywhere, so it might be a while, but it will be fun to pick away at. And while I was there I found out about a bunch of groups that meet weekly in the area. I haven't gotten a chance to check them out yet, but I definitely want to.

Before that was camping with Adriane, Emily and Kathryn. That was alot of fun. We went to River Otter State Part in Baldwinville mass. It was a nice little spot, and really empty. That was forever ago, so I don't remember a bunch of it.

Tuesday, Wednesday and Thursday were work days...Mmm work, unexciting etc etc...

Except on Tuesday Kathryn and I went to the learn how to be a DJ thing for ze radio show, which is wicked exciting, and I cant even wait. And then that night we watched Pee Wee's Big Adventure, in hopes of coming up with a cool name for our radio show. I think we're gonna do it again with other movies too.  

My dad left to go on vacation on Thursday, and I watched the house for them. That was kinda fun. I like having the house to myself. Well, except for the dishes. Friday I biked to Salem to go see a jazz band with Kathryn. I got a flat tire when I was almost home...My uncle patched it up for me, but then the brake cable was tightened, so my pads were pressing up against my tire, making it really hard to go. Of course, I didn't realize till I was half way up canal street on my way to Kathryn's house, so I ended up having to go back later that night. then we went to the show, which ended up being 21+, so we just sat in the hall and listened for a bit, which was actually kind of nice.

later that night Kathryn came back to my Hamilton house with me, and ended up spending the weekend there. Emily came by too for a little bit. We played cards, talked, played tennis, visited my grandma, cause all my tennis balls are at her house, and we needed some. My aunt and uncle were there too, cause the cancer walk was on Sunday. I wasn't able to make it there :( 

Sunday Kathryn and I headed back to Salem...We trained, which was good, cause my tire it flat again...I'm gonna have to use my next check to have it looked at :( instead of doing fun stuff with it. I'm definitely gonna need a new inner tube, and if I was smart I would have a tune up done while it was there, but I probably won't cause I'm cheap. 

anyhow, after that I trained up to newburyport to have birthday dinner with Adriane, Emily, Meredith, Traveling Buddy and Amy, which was super fun and way delicious...Mmm steak. we were gonna tent in Merediths back yard, but it was pouring, so we were like "Adriane's living room!" but her mom was being dumb, so it ended up being Emily's living room. we played apples to apples and it ended up being a way fun game. Meredith was being all ridiculous, and tired, and so was Emily, and it was like one huge giggle fest.

Then this morning we all woke up super early to go meet the ES class at the Lawrence damn, cause they're all on the river trip. It was good to see Mr. Saulnier again, and Mrs McMillan was there too. and Mr. king, but I didn't really talk to him a whole bunch. I was hoping Mr. Vercellone would be there too, but apparently he had to leave to go to a conference. They had wicked shitty weather for the last two days boo!

But seeing them doing the river trip made us want to do a river trip, which would would be wicked cool and I really want to do it. 

After that we decided it was a good idea to go to the beach, even though its miserable out. we caught a small break in the weather and tried to body surf, but failed miserably...the waves were big, but it was high tide so they were breaking really close to the shore...I got sand burn like woah...and the water was freezing...then junk food and apples to apples at Adriane's...and then home...and now I'm pretty close to sleep...

sooo...jeff over dosed on heroin in my bathroom on friday...it was just about the scariest thing ive ever experienced in my whole life. i really thought he was dead, his face was blue and for a while he wasnt breathing. my mom had started cpr and then realized that youre supposed to call for help first.

thats when i came down stairs and my mom threw the phone at me and told me to call an ambulence. my mom had him relativly stable when the emts showed up. if it wasnt such a stupid situation the emts would have been mildly entertaining. instead they were just annoying. they were making jokes and dodging vomit, that sort of stuff. they wrapped him in a sheet and carried him down the staris on a chair and he spent the night in the hospital

what gets to me the most is that i was sitting on the couch like twenty feet away when it happened. in fact i was waiting for him to get out of the bathroom so i could get my pjs.he was detoxing from the prescription drugs and i thought he was feeling sick so i left him alone and got a new pair from upstaires.

my sisters were in their bedrooms which are right next to the bathroom. they didnt wake up, which is a miracle, but the officers had to report it to dss, so now we have to deal with them conducting an investigation. mmm...fun

my mom had tried to throw him out twice in the previous 2 days and he came back both times. once he just ignored her and once i think he was to high to remember he got kicked out. my sisters were both home for the holiday and my mom didnt want to let them see them fight espcially in case it got physical, so she just let him stay instead of confronting him. i dont blame her at all, it is a diffecult situation and she handled it as well as can be expected i guess.

plus i think she felt guilty cause when brownie was going through the same thing she pushed him away and it ended poorly. i think she thought that if she didnt give up on him it would turn out differently. i wasnt really home enough in the past couple of weeks to feel like i saw enough to form an opinion, so i kinda just stood behind whatever my mom did figuring that she needed the support.

i was kinda shook up for a couple of days. i slept im my moms bed that night, balled my eyes out, and i still freak out every time i hear a wierd noise or a car slows in front of my house. not to mention the horrible mental images i get every time i go to the bathroom.

sunday morning, the next day, my mom called the fire deptartment, and had them unlock his truck, cause the keys were locked in it. then she was gonna fill it with all his shit and drive it to his mothers house, only while she and jen were upstairs packing, he came and took his truck. they loaded it all in jens truck and my mom was gonna drop me off at wallgreen while she went to the police to get a restraining order, only he was in his truck in the walgrees parking lot passed out.

we went to the police and told them, and found out that the situation doesnt qualify for a restraining order. the cops went and found him, and he said he wanted to go to the hosptal. once again, he was discharged the following day. i think that because he was a junky before for so long he knew what to say that would keep him out of jail.

so yeah...thats my life right now. on the bright side i can be assured he wont come back.

so my mom just told me a bunch of stuff about whats been going on with jeff and i need a place to put it.

apparently, the meds he is on is for liver pain caused by the hep c. about 9 months ago, my mom had a pinched nerve in her sholder, so jeff gave her some of said meds, which in turn made him run out early. she thinks this is when he started supplimenting with street drugs.

he went to the doctor who said that the meds are easy to build up a tolerence to, so its important to not increase the dossage, but rather take it more times, but in smaller doses. this he basically didnt know throught the 2 years he was on the drugs, and never had a problem refilling his prescription. and if he did, we're right down the street from rainbow terrace and the point.

he is now no longer on the meds, because his doctor thinks that he isnt actually having liver pains, as there is no nerve endings in the liver. the only place pain can come from is inflamation, which he shows no signs of. he is now detoxing from the meds and street drugs to go to another doctor to find out if it is actually gastro intestinal crap. he needs to be clean for two weeks to do that and he has 4 days so far.

hes also had several reasons for manic depression, including loosing his license, not being to get a steady job because of his record, and studying to pass a lpn test(uber hard no one passes thing), which he did and couldnt do anything with because of his cory.and that whole dead dad thing...and his mom is a bitch.

im kinda mad about the whole prescription drug doctor thing, cause i had to watch the same thing happen to brownie. the first thing he said when they were talking about putting him on oxycotton was he was a recovering drug addict, and they needed to be carefull, which was completly ignored and he never had a problem getting more legal heroin. 

in a sense im kinda mad at my mom for doing this, but i figure that he really wants to clean up his act, and thats the difference between him and brownie. you can tell he really wants to, he just has alot stacked against him and its not an easy thing. and lets face it, he doesnt stand a chance on the streets. he would most likey die between the illness and the drugs, and id rather have my mom fight diffecult battle then feel like she didnt do anything to prevent his death.

he also did alot to help her through a very diffecult part of her life and although this requires a bit more sacrifice, it wouldnt be right to just give up on him.

i just hope it ends soon.
